2
00:01:43,570 --> 00:01:48,980
Suryavansham.. Suryavansham.

3
00:01:56,450 --> 00:02:01,091
The light, the lion's roar.

4
00:02:02,489 --> 00:02:07,799
The kind, honest.

5
00:02:09,029 --> 00:02:14,339
Spark in your eyes
and glow on your face.

6
00:02:15,301 --> 00:02:21,012
The brilliance of sun,
coolness of the moon.

7
00:02:21,542 --> 00:02:25,816
You are the pilgrim for all of us.

8
00:02:28,014 --> 00:02:32,923
You're Lord Ram of
this modern world.

9
00:02:34,421 --> 00:02:41,167
Today on your birthday
we've come to wish you.

10
00:02:43,564 --> 00:02:49,141
Suryavansham.. Suryavansham.

11
00:02:49,870 --> 00:02:55,481
Suryavansham.. Suryavansham.

12
00:02:56,209 --> 00:03:01,787
Suryavansham.. Suryavansham.

13
00:03:29,142 --> 00:03:30,210
Hang on, sir.

14
00:03:32,479 --> 00:03:33,547
Look at this.

15
00:03:33,614 --> 00:03:37,053
Sister-in-law, your drape is not
held properly. Hold it properly.

16
00:03:37,117 --> 00:03:38,185
Mother.

17
00:03:46,826 --> 00:03:48,329
This is offering.

18
00:03:49,563 --> 00:03:51,265
l'd gone to the
temple to pray for father.

19
00:03:51,498 --> 00:03:55,539
First tell me. Have you
eaten something since morning?

20
00:03:59,839 --> 00:04:04,081
l've kept a fast for
father's sake. Take this.

21
00:04:06,780 --> 00:04:10,787
The whole snap.. Take the offering.
- Offering?

22
00:04:12,218 --> 00:04:13,286
Where did it come from?

23
00:04:13,987 --> 00:04:18,261
One of our servants has
prayed for your long life.

24
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:29,271
Once a person is born,
his life only shortens.

25
00:04:29,470 --> 00:04:30,538
lt doesn't become long. Take this.

26
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:36,111
Start.
- Sir, has everybody come?

27
00:04:37,043 --> 00:04:38,178
Yes, everybody has come.

28
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:43,083
Call Heera too.

29
00:04:47,386 --> 00:04:48,456
Take the photo.

30
00:04:54,027 --> 00:04:56,297
Greeting sir. - Greeting sir.
Greetings. Greetings.

31
00:04:56,362 --> 00:04:57,932
Sit. Sit. Sit.

32
00:05:02,135 --> 00:05:03,771
Accountant.
- Yes, sir.

33
00:05:05,104 --> 00:05:09,781
Whenever l see these people,
my desire..

34
00:05:09,843 --> 00:05:15,253
..to open a free hospital
for these poor people rouses.

35
00:05:17,017 --> 00:05:19,020
God knows when my
dream will be fulfilled.

36
00:05:19,118 --> 00:05:20,187
lt will be fulfilled, sir.

37
00:05:20,854 --> 00:05:24,293
You've fulfilled the dream
of 18 people in this village.

38
00:05:24,958 --> 00:05:27,195
Then how can your
wish not be fulfilled?

39
00:05:27,293 --> 00:05:30,433
Sir.. sir.
- What happened, Haria?

40
00:05:31,364 --> 00:05:33,902
Sir, my daughter..
- What happened to your daughter?

41
00:05:34,501 --> 00:05:36,303
She was going to get
married in the next week.

42
00:05:36,436 --> 00:05:39,308
Now she won't get married, sir.
- Why?

43
00:05:40,173 --> 00:05:41,241
Kevada Thakur.

44
00:05:42,476 --> 00:05:43,811
What did Kevada Thakur do?

45
00:05:44,344 --> 00:05:47,851
My daughter works at
Kevada Thakur's place.

46
00:05:48,849 --> 00:05:51,053
Yesterday she fell sick.

47
00:05:51,985 --> 00:05:55,024
So my daughter Kamali went for work.

48
00:06:10,169 --> 00:06:11,238
Wow!

49
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:32,929
Aren't you Parvati's daughter?
- Yes, sir.

50
00:06:33,093 --> 00:06:35,465
You are going to get married,
aren't you? - Yes, sir.

51
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:38,332
Do you know about wedding night?

52
00:06:39,466 --> 00:06:41,903
Do you know what it is all about?

53
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:47,143
Do you know how to please a man?

54
00:06:50,276 --> 00:06:52,547
You don't know? Learn it from me.

55
00:06:54,047 --> 00:06:56,184
A woman should be skilled in this.

56
00:06:57,551 --> 00:07:00,389
Otherwise the husband
banishes the wife from the house.

57
00:07:01,922 --> 00:07:02,990
Come.

58
00:07:05,291 --> 00:07:11,369
No! No! - Come! No!
No! - Listen to me! Come!

59
00:07:11,432 --> 00:07:12,500
Come.

60
00:07:16,336 --> 00:07:17,839
Listen, come on!

61
00:07:22,008 --> 00:07:23,778
l'll complain about this
in the village committee.

62
00:07:23,844 --> 00:07:25,447
And l'll disgrace you
in the whole village.

63
00:07:25,512 --> 00:07:26,780
l won't spare you.

64
00:07:30,216 --> 00:07:32,988
Jagia, where did the girl go?
- Towards the fields, sir.

65
00:07:33,052 --> 00:07:35,190
She was saying that she'll
complain to the village committee.

66
00:07:35,321 --> 00:07:38,795
Really? There was no fire and
already the smoke is curling out.

67
00:07:44,465 --> 00:07:46,201
Fool! Idiot!
- No!

68
00:07:46,399 --> 00:07:48,002
You were stealing in Thakur's house?

69
00:07:48,802 --> 00:07:50,070
You threatened him that..

70
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:51,371
..you will complaint against
him in the village committee.

71
00:07:52,071 --> 00:07:54,242
l'll not spare you! Go in!

72
00:07:55,074 --> 00:07:56,243
Lock her up!

73
00:08:03,783 --> 00:08:06,422
Now who will marry my daughter, sir?

74
00:08:08,021 --> 00:08:10,926
l can't even show
my face to anybody.

75
00:08:11,157 --> 00:08:12,225
Accountant.
- Yes, sir.

76
00:08:12,759 --> 00:08:13,994
Who is the inspector
in the police station?

77
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:15,128
He is some new inspector.

78
00:08:16,362 --> 00:08:17,431
Go to the police
station and tell him..

79
00:08:17,498 --> 00:08:19,100
..the girl is getting
married and leave her.

80
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:20,401
l'll handle all the proceedings.

81
00:08:20,934 --> 00:08:22,369
Who is this Bhanu Pratap Thakur?

82
00:08:23,069 --> 00:08:26,241
ls he SP.. DSP? Who is he?

83
00:08:26,305 --> 00:08:28,309
SP and DSP respect him too.

84
00:08:28,775 --> 00:08:29,843
He is an influential man and..

85
00:08:29,910 --> 00:08:31,480
..the leader of this
village community.

86
00:08:31,912 --> 00:08:35,786
l didn't get the post
of the police officer..

87
00:08:35,849 --> 00:08:39,890
..by the favour of leaders. l
got this post after studying law.

88
00:08:41,788 --> 00:08:44,359
Go and tell your
Bhanu Pratap Thakur.

89
00:08:45,025 --> 00:08:48,866
This is a police station,
not a village community.

90
00:08:49,395 --> 00:08:52,267
Where he can plough and reap a
harvest according to his will!

91
00:08:52,933 --> 00:08:54,201
Understood! Get out!

92
00:09:07,481 --> 00:09:09,183
Desh Rai Thakur.
- Sire.

93
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:12,754
Thakur Bhanu Pratap's man had come.

94
00:09:13,352 --> 00:09:14,989
To get the girl bailed out.

95
00:09:15,254 --> 00:09:18,027
Really? There was no fire
and the smoke is curling out.

96
00:09:18,291 --> 00:09:21,230
l didn't release the girl.
- Don't even do that.

97
00:09:21,995 --> 00:09:26,303
l'll pay you lavishly.
Listen. Do listen.

98
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:31,275
l'm sending stock of rice,
Ientil and pure ghee at your place.

99
00:09:31,337 --> 00:09:33,909
Sire, you iust relax.

100
00:09:34,307 --> 00:09:36,210
This girl will rot
in this prison only.

101
00:10:29,229 --> 00:10:30,832
What law have you studied?

102
00:10:32,065 --> 00:10:34,369
What do you know about law?
- Look..

103
00:10:34,434 --> 00:10:36,304
Under the Indian
criminal procedure court..

104
00:10:36,369 --> 00:10:39,943
..section 47 clause 2,
section 51, clause 2..

105
00:10:40,206 --> 00:10:43,312
..section 50 and 57
and according to..

106
00:10:43,376 --> 00:10:46,181
..the Supreme court
judgment dated 1983.

107
00:10:47,380 --> 00:10:49,451
lf there is a
proceeding involving women..

108
00:10:50,383 --> 00:10:51,853
..then a female police
officer should arrest her..

109
00:10:51,918 --> 00:10:54,523
..and a female
officer should search her.

110
00:10:54,588 --> 00:10:56,223
Did you do this? No.

111
00:10:58,992 --> 00:11:00,795
Arrested women should be presented..

112
00:11:00,860 --> 00:11:02,464
..before the court within 24 hours.

113
00:11:03,063 --> 00:11:04,800
Did you do this? No.

114
00:11:07,434 --> 00:11:09,805
lf for some reason she can't
be presented before the court..

115
00:11:09,869 --> 00:11:13,142
..then she is kept in
the prison for females.

116
00:11:13,339 --> 00:11:15,176
Did you do this? No.

117
00:11:18,111 --> 00:11:20,850
And you say that you got
this post after studying law.

118
00:11:21,481 --> 00:11:24,955
How did the police
department give you this post?

119
00:11:25,251 --> 00:11:26,988
What law and order?

120
00:11:27,921 --> 00:11:28,989
Accountant.
- Yes, sir.

121
00:11:29,355 --> 00:11:30,891
Call the SP.
- Yes, sir.

122
00:11:32,358 --> 00:11:34,896
Sir, could l have his number?

123
00:11:35,495 --> 00:11:37,065
39522.

124
00:11:38,965 --> 00:11:41,537
Hello.
- Sir, hang on. Sir.

125
00:11:43,970 --> 00:11:46,408
Sir, this is Thakur
Bhanu Pratap Singh.

126
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:49,177
Sir, you? What can l do for you?

127
00:11:50,477 --> 00:11:55,587
The police officer of our
village is teaching me law.

128
00:11:56,216 --> 00:11:57,452
You're calling from
the police station?

129
00:11:57,951 --> 00:11:59,854
Yes. Unfortunately.

130
00:12:00,086 --> 00:12:01,823
Sir, give the
phone to the inspector.

131
00:12:02,222 --> 00:12:03,290
Accountant.

132
00:12:05,792 --> 00:12:06,860
Yes, sir.

133
00:12:06,926 --> 00:12:08,797
Shameless! The man
sitting before you..

134
00:12:08,862 --> 00:12:11,066
..is a high court in himself.

135
00:12:11,331 --> 00:12:13,034
And court shouldn't be
called in the police station.

136
00:12:13,366 --> 00:12:16,004
Do as he says.
- Yes, sir.

137
00:12:21,975 --> 00:12:23,411
Release the girl.
- Yes, sir.

138
00:12:35,321 --> 00:12:37,391
Sir, leave the prison's door open.

139
00:13:50,129 --> 00:13:51,833
Dad, what happened? What's
the matter? - Move aside!

140
00:14:00,139 --> 00:14:01,208
Have shame, rascal!

141
00:14:02,008 --> 00:14:03,778
Just by wearing the
turban they think..

142
00:14:03,844 --> 00:14:04,912
..that they've worn
the crown of respect.

143
00:14:05,178 --> 00:14:06,346
You all are cowards!

144
00:14:07,781 --> 00:14:11,822
You left behind loads of wealth,
but not a penny of respect.

145
00:14:12,218 --> 00:14:17,061
The villagers respect, honour
and worship that Bhanu Pratap..

146
00:14:17,323 --> 00:14:19,026
..and they don't respect me at all.

147
00:14:20,093 --> 00:14:22,832
As if there is a
calamity of respect.

148
00:14:23,363 --> 00:14:25,233
My disrespected ancestors!

149
00:14:25,832 --> 00:14:30,006
Because of your inability,
today l'd to go to the prison too.

150
00:14:31,137 --> 00:14:32,807
l'm ashamed that
hitherto l used to..

151
00:14:32,873 --> 00:14:34,876
..feel proud of
useless Thakurs like you all.

152
00:14:36,009 --> 00:14:37,077
lt's good that you all died.

153
00:14:37,210 --> 00:14:39,347
Otherwise today l
would have killed you all.

154
00:14:41,415 --> 00:14:44,454
l'll do the task that
you all couldn't do.

155
00:14:45,251 --> 00:14:48,323
l'll ruin the sun of
that Suryavanshi forever.

156
00:14:55,395 --> 00:14:57,065
Heera.
- Yes, brother.

157
00:14:57,531 --> 00:14:59,233
Some special guests
are coming from the town.

158
00:14:59,466 --> 00:15:01,268
Go to the guest house
and get the place cleaned.

159
00:15:01,435 --> 00:15:02,503
They'll stay there only.

160
00:15:02,936 --> 00:15:04,004
Fine.
- Okay.

161
00:15:08,775 --> 00:15:09,977
Sister, sit straight.

162
00:15:10,376 --> 00:15:11,445
Bhabhi, who is
coming from the village?

163
00:15:12,345 --> 00:15:14,382
Brother-in-law, what
will you do by knowing it?

164
00:15:15,315 --> 00:15:16,383
Yes, what will l do?

165
00:15:16,917 --> 00:15:19,489
Then do the work that
your brother has given you.

166
00:15:22,055 --> 00:15:23,123
Who are the guests who are coming?

167
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:25,860
l don't know. Must be
some special guests.

168
00:15:26,225 --> 00:15:28,396
All guests are special, Heera.

169
00:15:29,362 --> 00:15:32,201
But we become tired of serving them.

170
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:37,139
Phulva, your child is crying
and you're tending the goats.

171
00:15:37,404 --> 00:15:39,875
What to do? l'm alone.
What all things will l manage?

172
00:15:40,139 --> 00:15:43,346
Okay. We'll tend the goats.
You go and quieten your child.

173
00:15:43,410 --> 00:15:44,478
Fine.

174
00:15:52,419 --> 00:15:53,954
Who is walking in
the middle of the road?

175
00:15:54,488 --> 00:15:57,059
Hey, move aside!

176
00:15:58,124 --> 00:15:59,292
She's saying it to the goats not us!

177
00:15:59,359 --> 00:16:01,497
ldiots! Can't you hear the horn!

178
00:16:02,062 --> 00:16:04,166
We can hear. But
the goats can't hear.

179
00:16:04,230 --> 00:16:05,433
Don't you have this
much of common sense?

180
00:16:06,132 --> 00:16:07,200
What did you say?

181
00:16:07,333 --> 00:16:08,803
l spoke in English.
You won't understand.

182
00:16:09,302 --> 00:16:12,207
Uncle, go and move those idiots.
- Fine.

183
00:16:14,007 --> 00:16:15,109
l'll teach them a lesson.

184
00:16:17,243 --> 00:16:18,779
Are you tending to the goats or..

185
00:16:18,845 --> 00:16:20,882
..taking a newlywed
bride to the theatre?

186
00:16:21,014 --> 00:16:23,318
We don't know how to take
newlywed brides to the theatre.

187
00:16:23,783 --> 00:16:25,052
We're not married.

188
00:16:25,785 --> 00:16:29,225
Only bachelors can do this.
Now look at me.

189
00:16:30,289 --> 00:16:32,828
Uncle, what are you doing?
Move them quickly.

190
00:16:33,460 --> 00:16:38,135
Ma'am, these are goats. Not some
athlete, that they'll run like sheep.

191
00:16:40,834 --> 00:16:42,537
Where are you going
with so many goats?

192
00:16:42,969 --> 00:16:44,806
To get them admitted
to engineering college.

193
00:16:45,071 --> 00:16:47,041
Hey! Do you think l'm a fool!

194
00:16:47,941 --> 00:16:49,209
This road goes towards Bharatpur?

195
00:16:50,209 --> 00:16:51,813
lf you go this way, then
your hand will get hurt.

196
00:16:52,413 --> 00:16:53,815
Keep your hand down and then go.

197
00:16:55,214 --> 00:16:56,518
And listen.
- What?

198
00:16:57,083 --> 00:16:58,151
Why are you going to Bharatpur?

199
00:16:58,952 --> 00:17:02,091
l'll buy 2 buffaloes and get
them admitted to medical college.

200
00:17:02,489 --> 00:17:04,960
ldiot! Hang on. Don't go from there.

201
00:17:05,492 --> 00:17:07,294
The bridge is out.

202
00:17:07,894 --> 00:17:09,764
Bridge is out?
- Yes.

203
00:17:09,830 --> 00:17:12,201
Do one thing. Go back 10 kms.

204
00:17:12,766 --> 00:17:15,771
Then take a right, then take a
Ieft, then again take a right..

205
00:17:15,836 --> 00:17:17,873
..you will find Bharatpur.

206
00:17:19,973 --> 00:17:21,876
Let me sit.
- What happened, uncle?

207
00:17:23,877 --> 00:17:26,983
Go back 10 kms. The
bridge is out further.

208
00:17:27,180 --> 00:17:28,248
Oh my God!

209
00:17:30,383 --> 00:17:31,452
Where did you..

210
00:17:32,185 --> 00:17:35,057
That girl called us goats,
that man called us donkey.

211
00:17:35,456 --> 00:17:37,459
Let them die. They'll
wander in the jungle.

212
00:17:37,524 --> 00:17:38,792
Then they'll come to
their senses. Come.

213
00:17:41,795 --> 00:17:44,232
Hi, Narendra.
- Mr. Karan.

214
00:17:44,330 --> 00:17:47,135
He's my younger brother, Varun. -
Greetings. Hi. - Hello. - Narendra.

215
00:17:47,901 --> 00:17:48,969
Mummy and daddy are
nowhere to be seen.

216
00:17:49,102 --> 00:17:52,809
There was a case hearing in
the court. So they couldn't come.

217
00:17:52,939 --> 00:17:54,007
They'll come by tomorrow.
- Okay.

218
00:17:54,841 --> 00:17:56,878
By the way, she's my sister Radha.
- Greetings.

219
00:17:57,043 --> 00:17:58,111
Mr. Karan.
- Greetings.

220
00:17:58,378 --> 00:18:00,950
And he is my uncle, my
father's best friend. - l see.

221
00:18:01,181 --> 00:18:03,218
Retired Maior Ranieet Singh.
How do you do, sir? - Hello.

222
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:05,152
Come sir.
- Welcome.

223
00:18:05,218 --> 00:18:07,155
Please.
- Come, dear. - Come.

224
00:18:08,154 --> 00:18:10,024
Did you have any
trouble on the route?

225
00:18:10,757 --> 00:18:13,896
No. We iust met 2
shepherds who fooled us.

226
00:18:14,194 --> 00:18:17,401
They made us travel 20 miles extra.
And wasted our time.

227
00:18:19,065 --> 00:18:20,367
Who? l don't understand.

228
00:18:23,036 --> 00:18:24,939
Heera! Come here!

229
00:18:30,944 --> 00:18:32,012
Hide your face carefully.

230
00:18:40,421 --> 00:18:41,790
Who are the
shepherds in our village?

231
00:18:43,424 --> 00:18:44,492
Nobody.
- What?

232
00:18:45,459 --> 00:18:46,527
Nobody.

233
00:18:47,093 --> 00:18:49,465
Who could it be?
Anyway, we'll find out.

234
00:18:50,129 --> 00:18:52,367
You take a rest.
- Okay. - Please.

235
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:55,503
Heera.
- Yes. - Take care of them.

236
00:18:56,135 --> 00:18:57,204
Okay, brother.

237
00:18:59,906 --> 00:19:02,010
Hey! Bring the luggage from the car.

238
00:19:12,385 --> 00:19:13,454
So heavy.

239
00:19:13,987 --> 00:19:16,959
They've made you a servant.
- Come. That's it.

240
00:19:18,825 --> 00:19:24,202
Wow! What a beauty! Beautiful!

241
00:19:28,167 --> 00:19:30,372
This is an old knife.

242
00:19:33,907 --> 00:19:36,879
Uncle, this is not a knife.
It is a sword.

243
00:19:37,376 --> 00:19:41,017
l know it is a sword. It
was a slip of the tongue.

244
00:19:44,985 --> 00:19:48,459
Wow! The servants here
read newspaper. - Stop!

245
00:19:49,823 --> 00:19:52,461
Why are you both hiding your
face since the time we've come?

246
00:19:52,959 --> 00:19:54,796
Today Lord Hanuman
has kept a fast for us.

247
00:19:55,462 --> 00:19:57,933
l mean, we have kept
Lord Hanuman's fast.

248
00:19:58,098 --> 00:19:59,835
Today we won't see any girl's face.

249
00:20:00,133 --> 00:20:01,201
Radha.
- Yes.

250
00:20:02,068 --> 00:20:03,270
This voice is very familiar.

251
00:20:03,470 --> 00:20:05,941
You must have heard it.
On B.B.C or Doordarshan.

252
00:20:06,372 --> 00:20:10,079
No. This is shepherds' voice.

253
00:20:10,811 --> 00:20:11,913
Hey! Turn around.

254
00:20:13,814 --> 00:20:14,882
Show your face.

255
00:20:15,015 --> 00:20:16,083
Okay.

256
00:20:16,149 --> 00:20:17,217
Turn around.

257
00:20:19,285 --> 00:20:20,353
Remove the newspaper.

258
00:20:24,090 --> 00:20:27,396
You guys? l'll say it to Thakur sir.

259
00:20:27,461 --> 00:20:29,832
No, no. Look, don't say
anything to Thakur sir.

260
00:20:30,363 --> 00:20:31,899
Henceforth we won't trouble you.

261
00:20:32,499 --> 00:20:33,834
Please forgive us.

262
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:35,570
Just saying sorry is not sufficient.

263
00:20:36,036 --> 00:20:38,273
You'll have to hold
your ears and sit.

264
00:20:38,905 --> 00:20:41,410
Yes, you do it.

265
00:20:43,043 --> 00:20:44,278
You too.
- Me too.

266
00:20:50,417 --> 00:20:51,919
Fine. Now go.

267
00:20:52,085 --> 00:20:53,153
Let's go.

268
00:21:02,328 --> 00:21:04,933
'These two made us
travel for 20 kms# 

269
00:21:05,264 --> 00:21:06,333
'l'll teach them a lesson# 

270
00:21:06,433 --> 00:21:07,501
Hey!

271
00:21:07,967 --> 00:21:09,036
Come here.

272
00:21:12,072 --> 00:21:16,246
ls there any laundry? l
mean one who irons clothes.

273
00:21:16,443 --> 00:21:18,446
No, you can tell it as laundry.

274
00:21:18,879 --> 00:21:20,181
l know English.

275
00:21:21,014 --> 00:21:22,951
He is illiterate.

276
00:21:23,149 --> 00:21:24,886
l didn't ask your bio-data.

277
00:21:24,984 --> 00:21:26,888
Tell me, is there a laundry here?

278
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:30,894
There is laundry, sweet maker,
tailor, butcher, washer man..

279
00:21:30,990 --> 00:21:32,427
Fine. Come with me.

280
00:21:40,467 --> 00:21:42,203
Take the clothes. Go
and get them ironed.

281
00:21:42,836 --> 00:21:44,406
l?
- Yes, you.

282
00:21:45,138 --> 00:21:46,508
Don't you remember,
what your boss had said?

283
00:21:46,873 --> 00:21:48,308
Do what work we give you.

284
00:21:48,975 --> 00:21:51,480
That is fine. But these
clothes are already ironed.

285
00:21:58,351 --> 00:22:01,791
Now there is a need for ironing.
- Yes.

286
00:22:02,088 --> 00:22:03,491
Then why are you looking
at it? Go and take it.

287
00:22:04,458 --> 00:22:05,526
Yes!

288
00:22:10,196 --> 00:22:11,264
Hey, you.

289
00:22:13,166 --> 00:22:16,540
Yes, l'm calling you.
- My name is Dharmendra.

290
00:22:16,836 --> 00:22:18,540
Heera calls me Mindra lovingly.

291
00:22:19,272 --> 00:22:22,946
l don't know all that.
You're just a fool for me.

292
00:22:24,177 --> 00:22:28,118
Do one thing. Take my clothes.
And get them ironed. Take it.

293
00:22:29,115 --> 00:22:30,818
What are you staring at? Take it.

294
00:22:31,284 --> 00:22:32,887
Shall l get it ironed
after sprinkling water?

295
00:22:32,953 --> 00:22:35,057
Yes. And use drinking water.

296
00:22:35,822 --> 00:22:39,361
Why drinking water.
l'll use mineral water.

297
00:22:45,899 --> 00:22:46,967
What are you doing?

298
00:22:47,033 --> 00:22:48,569
We have to wet the
clothes before ironing it.

299
00:22:48,902 --> 00:22:52,041
Beggar. l'll make the dogs
of this village run after him.

300
00:22:53,072 --> 00:22:55,978
Mindra. Again the
clothes will get dirty.

301
00:22:56,042 --> 00:22:57,945
Again we'll have to wash it.
Again we'll be told to iron it.

302
00:22:58,011 --> 00:22:59,346
We're treated worst than a servant.

303
00:22:59,513 --> 00:23:01,783
We've to do what they say.
We don't have any status.

304
00:23:02,015 --> 00:23:03,083
Heera, this is not fair.

305
00:23:03,149 --> 00:23:04,452
Mindra, listen to me.
- What?

306
00:23:04,918 --> 00:23:07,322
Look, they are special guests.
- So?

307
00:23:07,788 --> 00:23:08,856
Don't shout.

308
00:23:08,922 --> 00:23:10,959
Till the time they're here,
for my sake keep quiet.

309
00:23:11,492 --> 00:23:14,531
What for your sake! You don't
feel anything. Come, let's go.

310
00:23:15,996 --> 00:23:18,367
Left. A bit on the right.
- Is this fine?

311
00:23:18,532 --> 00:23:21,069
Forward. A bit on the side.
- What are you doing, uncle?

312
00:23:21,334 --> 00:23:23,071
Are you taking my
photo or making me parade?

313
00:23:23,269 --> 00:23:25,440
What to do? l can't see
your face in the camera.

314
00:23:25,806 --> 00:23:28,010
Sir, you'll see the face
only if you remove the cover.

315
00:23:28,341 --> 00:23:31,280
This is camera. No
need to remove the cover.

316
00:23:31,344 --> 00:23:33,347
Yes, it is a camera, not a cooker.

317
00:23:34,914 --> 00:23:36,818
l know. Do you think l'm a donkey?

318
00:23:37,217 --> 00:23:39,488
Hitherto l've never seen a donkey
taking a photo. What did you say?

319
00:23:40,253 --> 00:23:41,321
l'm iust moving my mouth.

320
00:23:41,387 --> 00:23:43,959
Shepherd, l'd given
you clothes for ironing.

321
00:23:44,024 --> 00:23:45,092
Where is that?

322
00:23:45,158 --> 00:23:49,165
Military sir, little mistake.
- What?

323
00:23:50,096 --> 00:23:52,935
The laundryman was drunk.
He fell on the ground.

324
00:23:53,333 --> 00:23:55,838
And the hot iron
fell on the clothes.

325
00:23:56,069 --> 00:23:57,204
All the clothes were burnt.

326
00:23:57,838 --> 00:23:59,508
With great difficulty.
l've saved a collar.

327
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:01,977
You can use it. Greetings.

328
00:24:12,385 --> 00:24:15,124
Hey! What are you doing with my car?

329
00:24:15,522 --> 00:24:17,391
Do you want to ruin
this too like my clothes?

330
00:24:17,524 --> 00:24:19,794
l'm washing it. Cleaning it.

331
00:24:19,860 --> 00:24:21,329
May you rot in hell!
Where is the other one?

332
00:24:21,428 --> 00:24:22,496
He has gone for lunch.

333
00:24:22,796 --> 00:24:24,298
Do you eat the whole day?

334
00:24:24,798 --> 00:24:26,033
We don't eat
without working like you.

335
00:24:26,266 --> 00:24:28,471
What did you say?
- l was just moving my mouth.

336
00:24:28,869 --> 00:24:30,939
Stop moving your mouth. And
start using your hands and legs.

337
00:24:31,471 --> 00:24:32,540
Fool!

338
00:24:33,039 --> 00:24:34,809
Sorry, sorry.
- What does this mean?

339
00:24:34,875 --> 00:24:36,878
l said sorry. To
hell with your sorry!

340
00:24:39,245 --> 00:24:41,817
Hey! - You're cleaning
my car with a broom?

341
00:24:41,915 --> 00:24:43,451
l'm cleaning it with a broom.
l'm not using sword.

342
00:24:44,183 --> 00:24:45,252
You!
- What are you doing?

343
00:24:47,120 --> 00:24:48,322
lt is not real.
- Really?

344
00:24:54,828 --> 00:24:55,896
Now do it.

345
00:25:07,774 --> 00:25:09,109
Sir. Sir.

346
00:25:09,375 --> 00:25:12,280
Your killing looks.
- Give me something.

347
00:25:12,345 --> 00:25:15,452
l'm hungry since the past 2 days.
- What!

348
00:25:20,954 --> 00:25:22,056
Throw the money, sir.

349
00:25:26,460 --> 00:25:28,463
l think you're in a
worst condition than me.

350
00:25:28,862 --> 00:25:30,932
l give more than this to beggars.

351
00:25:30,997 --> 00:25:32,332
Hey! Come here.

352
00:25:33,800 --> 00:25:35,235
From where did you
get these clothes?

353
00:25:35,902 --> 00:25:37,538
The owner of this
bungalow gave it to me.

354
00:25:38,237 --> 00:25:40,241
May God make him the
owner of garments' mill!

355
00:25:41,141 --> 00:25:42,209
Where is the collar?

356
00:25:42,342 --> 00:25:44,814
He removed it. He was
saying that a city dog..

357
00:25:44,878 --> 00:25:46,815
..has come in the house.

358
00:25:46,913 --> 00:25:47,981
Dog!
- Yes.

359
00:25:48,148 --> 00:25:49,451
He wanted a collar for his neck.

360
00:25:51,418 --> 00:25:52,820
See there. The owner has come.

361
00:25:56,189 --> 00:25:57,357
So he is the owner?

362
00:25:58,959 --> 00:26:01,163
Sir, why are you nervous?

363
00:26:01,428 --> 00:26:02,897
He is not a bigger donator than you.

364
00:26:03,163 --> 00:26:05,333
Look at this. This
beggar gave me 10 paisa.

365
00:26:08,201 --> 00:26:10,439
Owner? What?
- Did you call him?

366
00:26:10,504 --> 00:26:11,839
She is calling you.
- Who is it?

367
00:26:13,507 --> 00:26:16,512
Hey, where did he go? Where are you?

368
00:26:17,944 --> 00:26:22,486
My dear one. My little child.

369
00:26:22,916 --> 00:26:23,984
My dear one.

370
00:26:24,050 --> 00:26:25,787
What are you doing,
Phulva? Make the child quiet!

371
00:26:25,852 --> 00:26:26,920
Why are you making the child cry?

372
00:26:27,086 --> 00:26:28,790
lf he is not keeping quiet
even after giving him milk..

373
00:26:28,855 --> 00:26:29,923
..then what can l do?

374
00:26:29,990 --> 00:26:31,058
Then give him more.

375
00:26:32,058 --> 00:26:33,326
Keep quiet.

376
00:26:33,393 --> 00:26:34,462
Keep quiet.

377
00:26:40,867 --> 00:26:42,302
Keep quite!

378
00:26:42,802 --> 00:26:46,810
My heart, you are crazy.

379
00:26:48,475 --> 00:26:51,814
Sir is singing.
Now he'll keep quiet.

380
00:26:51,878 --> 00:26:55,351
You are crazy, l agree to it.

381
00:27:13,399 --> 00:27:17,106
My heart, you are crazy.

382
00:27:17,837 --> 00:27:21,512
You are crazy, l agree to it.

383
00:27:22,175 --> 00:27:26,216
You sigh each and every moment.

384
00:27:26,780 --> 00:27:30,787
Why are you afraid to say it?

385
00:27:31,084 --> 00:27:35,025
My heart, you are crazy.

386
00:28:30,777 --> 00:28:38,358
The rivers know that there
is thirst in the ocean too.

387
00:28:39,385 --> 00:28:43,326
l agree that the darkness is deep.

388
00:28:43,824 --> 00:28:47,798
Who has forbid you?

389
00:28:48,194 --> 00:28:51,366
Light the flame of the stars.

390
00:28:51,832 --> 00:28:56,073
Even dreams come true.

391
00:28:57,103 --> 00:29:01,277
l've heard so.

392
00:29:01,408 --> 00:29:05,047
My heart, you are crazy.

393
00:29:05,812 --> 00:29:09,452
You are mad, l agree to it.

394
00:29:10,216 --> 00:29:14,290
You sigh each and every moment.

395
00:29:14,754 --> 00:29:18,929
Why are you afraid to say it?

396
00:29:48,855 --> 00:29:50,224
Uncle, how much sugar for you?

397
00:29:50,790 --> 00:29:51,993
Just a bit. Not much.

398
00:29:52,358 --> 00:29:54,061
Oh, mummy and daddy have come.

399
00:29:56,830 --> 00:29:58,967
Hi, mom! Him dad!
- Hi, dad.

400
00:30:00,333 --> 00:30:01,536
How is everything here?
l'm fine, mummy.

401
00:30:02,068 --> 00:30:03,838
lt's beautiful.
- What is beautiful?

402
00:30:04,204 --> 00:30:06,909
The village is beautiful,
people here are beautiful.

403
00:30:06,973 --> 00:30:09,812
Come, uncle. Heera.
- Yes.

404
00:30:10,810 --> 00:30:13,215
Bring the luggage.
- Yes. Come. Come.

405
00:30:15,281 --> 00:30:17,819
lt's a beautiful place. Radha.
- Yes.

406
00:30:18,818 --> 00:30:21,824
Why are you saying to him
to carry the luggage? - Him?

407
00:30:21,888 --> 00:30:23,424
Yes.
- He's the servant.

408
00:30:23,557 --> 00:30:24,859
Servant.
- Yes.

409
00:30:25,959 --> 00:30:27,394
His face is similar to Thakur sir.

410
00:30:29,328 --> 00:30:33,905
Dear.. are you Thakur
Bhanu Pratap's son? - Yes.

411
00:30:39,440 --> 00:30:40,508
Why are you carrying this luggage?

412
00:30:40,574 --> 00:30:42,411
Keep it. l'll carry it.
- No, no. You're my guest.

413
00:30:42,476 --> 00:30:43,845
lt is my duty to serve you.

414
00:30:44,210 --> 00:30:45,846
Dear, it's your greatness.

415
00:30:46,246 --> 00:30:48,551
But l don't like it. Give it to me.

416
00:30:49,416 --> 00:30:51,453
You go home and make
arrangements for tomorrow's function.

417
00:30:52,051 --> 00:30:53,120
Function?

418
00:30:53,186 --> 00:30:55,256
Yes. Tomorrow your sister is
getting engaged to my son.

419
00:30:58,291 --> 00:30:59,494
Why? Don't you know?

420
00:31:08,234 --> 00:31:09,302
Sit.
- Sit.

421
00:31:10,270 --> 00:31:11,806
She is our relative.
- Greetings.

422
00:31:22,215 --> 00:31:27,960
Greetings. - Greetings.
Greetings. - God bless you.

423
00:31:29,889 --> 00:31:30,958
Greetings.

424
00:31:34,127 --> 00:31:35,195
Sit down, child.

425
00:31:37,163 --> 00:31:40,335
Priest has come. Let's ask him
for the auspicious time. Yes.

426
00:31:41,134 --> 00:31:43,037
So priest, which day is auspicious.

427
00:31:43,169 --> 00:31:46,074
Thakur sir, for the
wedding 10th is good day.

428
00:31:46,406 --> 00:31:49,913
But for the give away 10th and
1 1th, both the days are bad.

429
00:31:51,377 --> 00:31:54,316
So, we'll arrange for the give
away on the 12th. Fine. - Great.

430
00:32:09,362 --> 00:32:11,299
Grandpa. l love you, grandpa.

431
00:32:11,397 --> 00:32:14,437
A knee, a toe and here we go..
Listen. Where's Mr. Heera?

432
00:32:15,001 --> 00:32:16,069
l don't know.

433
00:32:16,135 --> 00:32:18,441
Uncle never comes before grandpa.
- Why?

434
00:32:19,506 --> 00:32:22,143
Grandpa doesn't like uncle.

435
00:32:30,116 --> 00:32:32,253
Enough, mother.
- One more.

436
00:32:33,487 --> 00:32:34,555
Open your mouth.

437
00:32:36,022 --> 00:32:40,029
Your father fixed your sister's
engagement just out the blue.

438
00:32:41,361 --> 00:32:44,233
l had no idea dear,
that you don't know.

439
00:32:45,832 --> 00:32:47,267
What would l have done
even if l'd known, mother?

440
00:32:48,835 --> 00:32:53,276
l know that my status in
this house is that of a servant.

441
00:32:54,575 --> 00:32:57,279
And servant shouldn't be
told each and every thing.

442
00:32:59,479 --> 00:33:00,481
Mother.

443
00:33:02,883 --> 00:33:04,786
Mother, if there is reincarnation..

444
00:33:04,851 --> 00:33:08,425
..then l would like to be
your and father's son again.

445
00:33:11,124 --> 00:33:12,794
What l couldn't get in this birth..

446
00:33:12,859 --> 00:33:15,230
..maybe l'll get it in that life.

447
00:33:20,333 --> 00:33:23,473
Mindra. - What? Again you
want to get your clothes ironed?

448
00:33:24,170 --> 00:33:26,274
l want to know something
about Mr. Heera from you.

449
00:33:28,475 --> 00:33:29,877
Why are you looking like this?

450
00:33:30,376 --> 00:33:33,181
Because hitherto nobody has
addressed Heera as Mr. Heera.

451
00:33:34,448 --> 00:33:35,516
What do you want to know?

452
00:33:36,417 --> 00:33:38,286
Thakur sir is an
influential figure in this village.

453
00:33:38,819 --> 00:33:40,822
One of his sons is doctor
and the other is engineer.

454
00:33:41,287 --> 00:33:42,823
Then why is Mr. Heera like this?

455
00:33:43,424 --> 00:33:45,393
Why is he treated like a servant?

456
00:33:45,992 --> 00:33:47,294
Even he is Thakur sir's son.

457
00:33:47,428 --> 00:33:50,266
Yes. But Thakur doesn't
consider him as his son.

458
00:33:50,497 --> 00:33:51,565
Why?

459
00:33:54,568 --> 00:33:56,103
Heera attended
school when he was a kid.

460
00:33:56,837 --> 00:33:58,239
But he was very weak in studies.

461
00:33:59,840 --> 00:34:01,777
He always used to flunk in exams.

462
00:34:03,376 --> 00:34:05,781
Thinking that he'll get
father's beatings if he went home..

463
00:34:05,846 --> 00:34:09,954
..with O marks, he used
to convert O into 100.

464
00:34:10,851 --> 00:34:13,489
But still he would get beatings.
- Why?

465
00:34:14,421 --> 00:34:17,794
Because he didn't know how
many zeros there are in 100.

466
00:34:18,425 --> 00:34:21,329
He sometimes used to put 4
zeros and sometimes 5 zeros.

467
00:34:23,363 --> 00:34:25,366
Heera was not at all
interested in studies.

468
00:34:26,366 --> 00:34:28,069
He used to go to school
only for Gauri's sake.

469
00:34:28,502 --> 00:34:30,371
Gauri? Who is Gauri?

470
00:34:31,304 --> 00:34:32,907
Thakur sir's friend's daughter.

471
00:34:34,541 --> 00:34:37,312
Gauri's parents died when she
was a child, in a car accident.

472
00:34:38,412 --> 00:34:40,482
Thakur sir brought Gauri home.

473
00:34:41,381 --> 00:34:43,853
And Gauri and Heera used
to go to school together.

474
00:34:44,885 --> 00:34:48,258
Heera liked Gauri.
Gauri wanted to study.

475
00:34:48,889 --> 00:34:51,193
But Heera always used to
distract her with games.

476
00:34:52,292 --> 00:34:53,360
Gauri could never study.

477
00:34:54,828 --> 00:34:56,163
One day when both of
them went to school..

478
00:34:56,830 --> 00:35:00,404
'Stand up. Why didn't you
do your homework? Tell me# 

479
00:35:01,001 --> 00:35:02,069
'Forward your hand# 

480
00:35:03,437 --> 00:35:06,175
'Mother! Mother!'

481
00:35:09,443 --> 00:35:10,511
'Mother!'

482
00:35:13,212 --> 00:35:14,281
'Let's go, Gauri# 

483
00:35:22,055 --> 00:35:23,357
'Heera, get up# 

484
00:35:23,957 --> 00:35:25,794
'Along with the books,
Heera's education..

485
00:35:25,859 --> 00:35:26,927
..also got washed
away in the water# 

486
00:35:29,095 --> 00:35:33,336
Heera hated the school
where Gauri was beaten.

487
00:35:34,468 --> 00:35:37,306
From that day, he didn't
even look at that school.

488
00:35:38,805 --> 00:35:40,808
Thinking that in the
company of Heera..

489
00:35:40,874 --> 00:35:42,811
..Gauri's studies
will be badly affected..

490
00:35:42,876 --> 00:35:44,446
..Thakur sir sent
Gauri to study in the city.

491
00:35:45,512 --> 00:35:46,914
Heera and Gauri got separated.

492
00:35:47,448 --> 00:35:50,954
They grew up separately.
Heera was always sad.

493
00:35:52,318 --> 00:35:53,386
But there was one
source of happiness.

494
00:35:54,020 --> 00:35:55,456
Gauri used to come from
