Me? Consider me your friend,

1700
02:14:34,775 --> 02:14:35,843
Friend?

1701
02:14:35,909 --> 02:14:38,514
Yes. Am l not
capable to be your friend?

1702
02:14:38,812 --> 02:14:41,784
Your friendship is better
than even the elephant ride.

1703
02:14:42,816 --> 02:14:45,454
Ok friend. My bus is here. Bye!

1704
02:14:45,519 --> 02:14:47,489
Hey Listen.. take your bag..

1705
02:14:47,554 --> 02:14:50,459
Ok. Bye. See you again.

1706
02:15:15,915 --> 02:15:19,490
Very good. You have
had sweets. Come on!

1707
02:15:20,487 --> 02:15:26,064
Another. Come on. Just one more.
- Enough. l wont eat now.

1708
02:15:27,494 --> 02:15:28,562
Open your mouth. Open.

1709
02:15:31,832 --> 02:15:32,900
What is this?

1710
02:15:32,966 --> 02:15:36,673
Your tooth has been taken by a rat.
- How could he?

1711
02:15:37,170 --> 02:15:40,677
Friend, children lose their teeth.

1712
02:15:40,740 --> 02:15:44,047
Then they get new teeth. Oh!

1713
02:15:47,814 --> 02:15:50,185
Friend, won't the
elephant come today?

1714
02:15:50,950 --> 02:15:53,088
Why? Do you want to ride him?

1715
02:15:53,620 --> 02:15:57,561
Yes. - Come on. Today
l'll be the elephant.

1716
02:15:57,624 --> 02:16:01,765
Come.
- Come on, elephant.

1717
02:16:04,665 --> 02:16:06,468
Move, elephant!

1718
02:16:06,533 --> 02:16:08,536
Come on, elephant.

1719
02:16:08,835 --> 02:16:09,903
Look at sir.

1720
02:16:09,969 --> 02:16:17,217
- Come on. Come on move faster!
Run! Move elephant! -

1721
02:16:17,644 --> 02:16:18,779
Come on, elephant.

1722
02:16:18,845 --> 02:16:21,049
Wait now. Get off.

1723
02:16:22,949 --> 02:16:25,921
Did you have fun?
- Yes. More than the elephant.

1724
02:16:25,985 --> 02:16:27,723
Ok, come.

1725
02:16:28,855 --> 02:16:34,131
Tell me, friend. Who else
do you have in your family?

1726
02:16:34,561 --> 02:16:36,698
Mummy, daddy and me.

1727
02:16:38,665 --> 02:16:42,238
ls that all? No one else?
- No.

1728
02:16:47,907 --> 02:16:53,519
Listen. l also have grandparents,
2 uncles and aunts.

1729
02:16:53,580 --> 02:16:55,517
But l don't know where do they live.

1730
02:16:57,183 --> 02:17:02,192
Who told you all this?
- My father told me.

1731
02:17:03,690 --> 02:17:04,825
What else did he tell you?

1732
02:17:04,891 --> 02:17:09,834
Grandfather didn't like my daddy.
So, he threw him out of the house.

1733
02:17:11,064 --> 02:17:14,036
Didn't he reveal why he didn't
like him? - He didn't study enough.

1734
02:17:14,100 --> 02:17:15,903
Grandfather is not
to blame for this.

1735
02:17:16,136 --> 02:17:20,010
lf l don't study,
daddy will be angry. Right?

1736
02:17:22,909 --> 02:17:26,048
Ok. Its time for me to go home. Bye.

1737
02:17:26,546 --> 02:17:30,086
Listen, take this home.

1738
02:17:30,150 --> 02:17:31,853
Thank you, friend.
l'll meet you tomorrow.

1739
02:17:35,221 --> 02:17:37,191
Listen, l've sent
the cards to everybody.

1740
02:17:37,758 --> 02:17:39,895
But father has still
not received the card.

1741
02:17:40,627 --> 02:17:42,129
He is going to do the inauguration.

1742
02:17:44,665 --> 02:17:49,541
Yes, Radha. He'll never see my face.

1743
02:17:51,505 --> 02:17:53,775
lt will be good if you
go and give him the card.

1744
02:17:54,875 --> 02:17:58,248
lf he comes, then l'll
think that he's not angry.

1745
02:17:59,245 --> 02:18:00,815
lf not then..
- Daddy.

1746
02:18:01,515 --> 02:18:02,583
Hey!

1747
02:18:03,684 --> 02:18:06,021
Take this. l've got sweets for you.

1748
02:18:07,654 --> 02:18:08,822
Who gave you this?

1749
02:18:09,255 --> 02:18:14,264
My friend. He was
saying that you love sweets.

1750
02:18:14,628 --> 02:18:15,696
Really?
- Yes.

1751
02:18:15,762 --> 02:18:17,030
Your friend?
- Yes.

1752
02:18:17,096 --> 02:18:18,934
l don't know any of your friends.

1753
02:18:19,700 --> 02:18:21,202
Then how did he come to
know about what l like.

1754
02:18:21,702 --> 02:18:22,770
He studies in your class?

1755
02:18:22,836 --> 02:18:24,873
No, he has already
completed his studies.

1756
02:18:25,171 --> 02:18:27,676
He has big beard and moustache.

1757
02:18:30,544 --> 02:18:31,612
Beard and moustache?

1758
02:18:31,678 --> 02:18:34,750
Yes. l befriended
him a few days back.

1759
02:18:36,282 --> 02:18:37,551
How does he look like?

1760
02:18:40,987 --> 02:18:42,222
l'll show you.

1761
02:18:46,660 --> 02:18:48,497
Don't eat it. God
knows who has given this.

1762
02:18:49,162 --> 02:18:52,234
The smell is very familiar.

1763
02:19:01,007 --> 02:19:04,547
Look at this, daddy.
My friend is like this.

1764
02:19:17,123 --> 02:19:18,659
He looks like you, doesn't he?

1765
02:19:18,725 --> 02:19:24,035
No, son. He doesn't look
like me. l look like him.

1766
02:19:25,832 --> 02:19:31,142
And listen.. if you
meet your friend. - Yes.

1767
02:19:32,071 --> 02:19:37,750
Then touch his feet.
You'll feel peaceful.

1768
02:19:39,112 --> 02:19:40,949
lf he keeps his hands on your head.

1769
02:19:48,054 --> 02:19:49,122
Father.

1770
02:19:50,824 --> 02:19:54,765
l was iust waiting for you.
l want to give this card.

1771
02:19:57,998 --> 02:20:02,039
l know.. l should have
come home to give the card.

1772
02:20:03,236 --> 02:20:07,110
But you've forbid us
to enter the house. So..

1773
02:20:08,809 --> 02:20:11,180
Your son has made a free
hospital for poor people..

1774
02:20:11,244 --> 02:20:13,081
..named after you.

1775
02:20:18,251 --> 02:20:22,158
His wish is that you
should inaugurate the hospital.

1776
02:20:22,756 --> 02:20:23,891
We will be pleased.

1777
02:20:38,805 --> 02:20:41,777
Listen, l'm going for the
inauguration of Heera's hospital.

1778
02:20:41,842 --> 02:20:43,110
What if father finds out?

1779
02:20:43,176 --> 02:20:45,481
That's why l'm saying in
case mother or father ask..

1780
02:20:45,546 --> 02:20:47,917
..tell them that
l've gone for shaving.

1781
02:20:47,981 --> 02:20:49,049
Okay.
- Okay.

1782
02:20:52,986 --> 02:20:54,054
Shall l also come?

1783
02:20:54,120 --> 02:20:56,959
What are you doing, Usha?
l'm myself going secretly.

1784
02:20:57,023 --> 02:20:58,526
Okay, only you can go.

1785
02:20:59,092 --> 02:21:02,799
lf somebody asks me, l'll tell
them you've gone to the barber.

1786
02:21:02,863 --> 02:21:04,499
Barber?
- Yes.

1787
02:21:04,565 --> 02:21:06,602
Okay. Thank you.

1788
02:21:11,671 --> 02:21:12,740
Grandma.
- Yes.

1789
02:21:12,806 --> 02:21:14,509
Are you also going for shaving?

1790
02:21:14,741 --> 02:21:15,876
Me and shaving?

1791
02:21:16,610 --> 02:21:17,678
Fine, grandma.

1792
02:21:17,744 --> 02:21:20,516
You can go for uncle
Heera's hospital inauguration.

1793
02:21:20,847 --> 02:21:24,521
lf grandpa asks, l'll tell him
that you've gone to the temple.

1794
02:21:25,251 --> 02:21:26,687
My dear grandchild.

1795
02:21:43,970 --> 02:21:45,038
Sharada.

1796
02:21:46,540 --> 02:21:48,710
Sharada.
- Nobody is at home, grandpa.

1797
02:21:49,476 --> 02:21:52,582
Why?
- Everybody has gone out, grandpa.

1798
02:21:52,646 --> 02:21:53,981
Out?
- Yes, grandpa.

1799
02:21:54,047 --> 02:21:56,151
Father and uncle have gone to town.

1800
02:21:56,215 --> 02:21:58,721
My mother and aunt
have gone to meet granny.

1801
02:21:58,785 --> 02:21:59,987
And grandma has gone to temple.

1802
02:22:05,892 --> 02:22:10,568
Look, l'm going for a
stroll in the garden.

1803
02:22:10,631 --> 02:22:13,503
lf your grandma
returns from the temple..

1804
02:22:13,567 --> 02:22:15,804
..tell her that l'll
be back till lunchtime.

1805
02:22:15,869 --> 02:22:16,937
Fine, grandpa.

1806
02:22:30,083 --> 02:22:31,151
Hello.
- Hello.

1807
02:22:38,257 --> 02:22:39,527
Will father come?

1808
02:22:41,995 --> 02:22:43,631
l'm sure that he'll come.

1809
02:22:49,202 --> 02:22:50,471
Ladies and gentlemen.

1810
02:22:51,871 --> 02:22:58,552
This hospital before you is the
result of only Heera's hard work.

1811
02:23:00,213 --> 02:23:03,720
The dream of building the
hospital was seen by Heera's father.

1812
02:23:04,985 --> 02:23:07,957
But due to some reason
it was not fulfilled.

1813
02:23:10,090 --> 02:23:13,497
After being banished
from father's house..

1814
02:23:13,560 --> 02:23:18,168
..travelling in a old bus,
Heera reached this destination.

1815
02:23:25,005 --> 02:23:27,242
Every parent has children.

1816
02:23:28,675 --> 02:23:31,514
But a child like Heera,
who makes his parents..

1817
02:23:31,578 --> 02:23:34,517
..fortunate, is born
only once in blue moon.

1818
02:23:41,522 --> 02:23:43,191
l don't think
father will come, Heera.

1819
02:23:45,892 --> 02:23:46,960
Fine, l'll do something.

1820
02:24:09,816 --> 02:24:12,488
Brothers and sister,
as you all know..

1821
02:24:12,553 --> 02:24:14,490
..Shri Bhanu Pratap Thakur was..

1822
02:24:14,555 --> 02:24:16,959
..going to inaugurate this hospital.

1823
02:24:17,991 --> 02:24:20,496
But as he had to go for
meeting of the village committee..

1824
02:24:20,561 --> 02:24:23,098
..he couldn't come here.

1825
02:24:23,664 --> 02:24:26,503
So he has sent a message
along with his blessings.

1826
02:24:27,501 --> 02:24:31,508
That his grandson,
Junior Bhanu Pratap Thakur..

1827
02:24:31,572 --> 02:24:32,740
..will inaugurate this hospital.

1828
02:25:00,834 --> 02:25:03,038
Thanks for coming here.

1829
02:25:03,537 --> 02:25:06,476
Firstly, l want to
tell you all something.

1830
02:25:07,841 --> 02:25:10,479
A few minutes ago sir had said..

1831
02:25:10,544 --> 02:25:13,716
..this hospital was father's
dream that he couldn't fulfil.

1832
02:25:16,516 --> 02:25:22,160
l want to say that there was
no work that father couldn't do.

1833
02:25:24,891 --> 02:25:29,099
Secondly, father didn't
banish me from the house.

1834
02:25:31,097 --> 02:25:36,106
To make me independent,
he separated me from him.

1835
02:25:42,075 --> 02:25:43,445
When a twig breaks from the tree..

1836
02:25:43,510 --> 02:25:46,014
..then the tree and
twig both feel pain.

1837
02:25:47,814 --> 02:25:49,784
l'm sure that my father
must have felt pain like me..

1838
02:25:49,850 --> 02:25:51,453
..in separating me from him.

1839
02:25:53,887 --> 02:25:57,461
People say.. the stone
that Feels pain by the..

1840
02:25:57,524 --> 02:26:00,930
..banging of the hammer..
it can never become an idol.

1841
02:26:02,028 --> 02:26:06,537
The field that is sad by
ploughing can never give yields.

1842
02:26:08,669 --> 02:26:12,476
Scolding of mother
and father are like..

1843
02:26:12,539 --> 02:26:17,482
..hammer and plough.. but
these scolding only teach us..

1844
02:26:17,544 --> 02:26:20,215
..enCOUra9eS US.

1845
02:26:23,483 --> 02:26:25,888
l was a useless fellow.

1846
02:26:27,053 --> 02:26:29,223
But whatever l'm today is
because of father's scolding.

1847
02:26:30,990 --> 02:26:33,496
lf today l'm
independent Then it is..

1848
02:26:33,560 --> 02:26:35,497
..because of father's encouragement.

1849
02:26:46,172 --> 02:26:48,075
My father loves me a lot.

1850
02:26:52,512 --> 02:26:56,520
lf today he comes to
know the language of fate..

1851
02:26:56,583 --> 02:27:00,089
..then he would have
touched my forehead.

1852
02:27:21,541 --> 02:27:25,816
Oh my God! So many people!
So much applaud!

1853
02:27:26,145 --> 02:27:28,718
So much commotion! So many praises!

1854
02:27:28,782 --> 02:27:29,850
You're talking about what?

1855
02:27:29,916 --> 02:27:31,819
Heera's hospital inauguration.

1856
02:27:33,286 --> 02:27:35,891
You'd gone there?
- Why would l go there?

1857
02:27:35,956 --> 02:27:38,828
Our neighbour Vimla
had gone. She told me.

1858
02:27:41,294 --> 02:27:43,966
He was talking only about
you in the entire speech.

1859
02:27:44,498 --> 02:27:46,768
You know what he
said in your praises?

1860
02:27:48,935 --> 02:27:53,009
He said that you are
responsible for his progress.

1861
02:27:53,774 --> 02:27:56,513
With your
encouragement and blessings..

1862
02:27:56,576 --> 02:27:58,747
..he was successful in
building the hospital.

1863
02:27:59,178 --> 02:28:03,521
And yes, for your
scolding he was saying..

1864
02:28:03,583 --> 02:28:08,794
..stone.. hammer..
plough, earth.. something..

1865
02:28:08,855 --> 02:28:10,525
No, he didn't say this.

1866
02:28:12,091 --> 02:28:14,196
l mean.. he might have said.

1867
02:28:14,961 --> 02:28:20,539
The stone that cries
with the banging of hammer..

1868
02:28:20,600 --> 02:28:24,608
..it can't be an idol.

1869
02:28:24,905 --> 02:28:28,545
The field that is
sad to be ploughed..

1870
02:28:28,608 --> 02:28:31,046
..it can't give yields.

1871
02:28:31,110 --> 02:28:32,213
Something in the similar lines.

1872
02:28:33,046 --> 02:28:34,816
Where did you hear all this?

1873
02:28:35,181 --> 02:28:37,619
lt is an old proverb.
l'd learn in the 4th class.

1874
02:28:39,886 --> 02:28:40,954
Why are you looking like this?

1875
02:28:41,755 --> 02:28:44,927
l'm seeing that you still
remember 4th class studies.

1876
02:28:44,991 --> 02:28:46,059
What is so great?

1877
02:28:46,125 --> 02:28:47,929
People remember A, B, C
taught in the 1st class.

1878
02:28:47,994 --> 02:28:50,833
Forget it. l thought
that you had gone there.

1879
02:28:52,231 --> 02:28:55,772
l spotted your clothes
right there in the crowd.

1880
02:28:56,636 --> 02:28:58,907
How did it go there?

1881
02:28:58,972 --> 02:29:03,981
l don't know. Hitherto it
used to be on your shoulder.

1882
02:29:04,511 --> 02:29:08,117
Maybe it walked on its own today.
It is modern world.

1883
02:29:08,181 --> 02:29:09,951
Anything can happen.

1884
02:29:14,253 --> 02:29:16,157
Dear Sonu, breakfast is ready.

1885
02:29:16,222 --> 02:29:19,127
Mummy, l'm late. l'll eat it later.

1886
02:29:19,759 --> 02:29:22,097
Hello, Sonu. Where are you going?

1887
02:29:22,963 --> 02:29:24,866
l'm going to meet my friend, daddy.

1888
02:29:25,566 --> 02:29:28,270
So today he's coming to meet you?

1889
02:29:28,935 --> 02:29:31,272
No, today l'm going to meet him.

1890
02:29:31,638 --> 02:29:34,275
Oh, so you're going to meet him.
- Yes.

1891
02:29:34,975 --> 02:29:36,043
What are you taking for him?

1892
02:29:36,910 --> 02:29:38,613
Nothing. What should l take?

1893
02:29:41,648 --> 02:29:45,221
Let's do one thing. Today
take 'Kheer' for him. - 'Kheer'?

1894
02:29:45,852 --> 02:29:49,693
Yes. - How do you know
that he likes 'Kheer'?

1895
02:29:50,524 --> 02:29:53,630
Like how he knows
that l like sweets.

1896
02:29:56,696 --> 02:29:58,934
Come, have breakfast.
And l'll prepare 'Kheer'.

1897
02:30:05,972 --> 02:30:09,244
'Where does he go
everyday at this time?'

1898
02:30:38,539 --> 02:30:39,741
Hi, buddy!

1899
02:30:43,777 --> 02:30:46,782
Hey! Come, come, come.
- Hi.

1900
02:30:49,916 --> 02:30:53,490
Sorry, buddy. l got late.
- No problem.

1901
02:30:53,554 --> 02:30:55,089
Okay. Let's go.

1902
02:31:01,495 --> 02:31:05,669
Buddy, you like 'Kheer', don't you?
- Who told you?

1903
02:31:05,732 --> 02:31:06,867
My daddy.

1904
02:31:06,933 --> 02:31:08,736
This child is Heera Thakur's son.

1905
02:31:09,135 --> 02:31:11,072
Senior Thakur comes here
everyday to meet this child.

1906
02:31:12,238 --> 02:31:13,674
What else did your daddy say?

1907
02:31:14,107 --> 02:31:16,912
He said you're like God.

1908
02:31:16,977 --> 02:31:21,251
He told me to greet
you when l see you.

1909
02:31:23,249 --> 02:31:27,524
Eat 'Kheer', buddy.
- l just had my breakfast.

1910
02:31:28,522 --> 02:31:32,596
l'll take this home.
l'll eat it there. - Okay.

1911
02:31:33,527 --> 02:31:34,595
Let's go.

1912
02:31:38,532 --> 02:31:41,169
Do come tomorrow. Bye.
- Bye.

1913
02:31:44,070 --> 02:31:45,138
Grandpa.

1914
02:31:51,111 --> 02:31:55,018
God knows why l felt
like calling you grandpa.

1915
02:31:55,081 --> 02:31:56,149
And l called you.

1916
02:32:14,234 --> 02:32:17,708
Henceforth you'll call me grandpa.
- Okay.

1917
02:32:18,972 --> 02:32:20,040
Go.

1918
02:32:36,156 --> 02:32:38,528
Sir, somebody has
fainted on the street.

1919
02:32:40,561 --> 02:32:41,562
Driver, stop the car.

1920
02:32:49,202 --> 02:32:50,471
Driver, give me the key.

1921
02:32:50,537 --> 02:32:51,672
No, nothing will happen with key.

1922
02:32:51,738 --> 02:32:52,940
Bring a piece of wood. Okay.

1923
02:32:54,474 --> 02:32:56,211
Hold his arms.
- Sir.

1924
02:33:11,024 --> 02:33:13,496
Yes. Come.
- Be careful.

1925
02:33:15,228 --> 02:33:17,900
You saved my life as
the messiah of God.

1926
02:33:18,498 --> 02:33:20,769
l'll always be indebted to you.

1927
02:33:20,834 --> 02:33:23,773
Okay, go carefully.
Take your luggage.

1928
02:33:35,181 --> 02:33:37,586
What happened, sir?
- Nothing.

1929
02:33:40,821 --> 02:33:41,822
Let's go, driver.

1930
02:33:50,797 --> 02:33:52,467
From where have you
brought this 'Kheer'?

1931
02:33:52,532 --> 02:33:53,668
One of my friends gave it to me.

1932
02:33:55,869 --> 02:33:59,208
Which friend?
- You don't know him.

1933
02:34:00,206 --> 02:34:01,475
He's my childhood friend.

1934
02:34:01,541 --> 02:34:05,048
ls he your childhood friend..
or a kid who is friend?

1935
02:34:23,062 --> 02:34:25,935
l know. You meet your grandson.

1936
02:34:30,136 --> 02:34:33,510
Yes, l meet him! l met him.

1937
02:34:33,573 --> 02:34:34,642
Why?

1938
02:34:36,843 --> 02:34:39,515
The one whom you
estranged from yourself..

1939
02:34:39,579 --> 02:34:41,517
..why so much of fervour for him?

